%U A394826 18416,20306,22321,24465,26742,29156,31711,34411,37260,40262,43421,46741,50226,53880
%N A394826 The tetrahemihexahedral numbers.
%C A394826 Submitted on behalf of a third-party: mecejide and ericabq from the Polytope Discord.
%H A394826 H. K. Kim, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1090/s0002-9939-02-06710-2">On regular polytope numbers</a>, Proceedings of the American Mathematical Society, 131(1), 65-75 (2002).
%H A394826 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Tetrahemihexahedron">Tetrahemihexahedron</a>.
%H A394826 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetrahemihexahedron">Tetrahemihexahedron</a>.
%H A394826 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (4,-6,4,-1).
%F A394826 a(n) = (n + 2)*(4*n^2 - 5*n + 3)/6.
%F A394826 From _Stefano Spezia_, May 30 2026: (Start)
%F A394826 G.f.: x*(1 + 2*x + 2*x^2 - x^3)/(1 - x)^4.
%F A394826 E.g.f.: exp(x)*(6 + 15*x^2 + 4*x^3)/6 - 1. (End)
%t A394826 a[n_] := (4*n^3 + 3*n^2 - 7*n + 6)/6; Array[a, 45] (* _Amiram Eldar_, May 30 2026 *)
%o A394826 (Python)
%o A394826 def A394826(n): return n*(n*(4*n+3)-7)//6+1 # _Chai Wah Wu_, Jun 05 2026
